{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This family represents E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase RNF4, a SUMO-targeted E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase with a pivotal function in the DNA damage response (DDR) through interacting with the deubiquitinating enzyme ubiquitin-specific protease 11 (USP11), a known DDR-component, and further facilitating DNA repair [[cite:PUB00093836]]. It plays a novel role in preventing the loss of intact chromosomes and ensures the maintenance of chromosome integrity. Moreover, RNF4 is responsible for the UbcH5A-catalyzed formation of K48 chains that target SUMO-modified promyelocytic leukemia (PML) protein for proteasomal degradation in response to arsenic treatment [[cite:PUB00063225]]. It also interacts with telomeric repeat binding factor 2 (TRF2) in a small ubiquitin-like modifiers (SUMO)-dependent manner and preferentially targets SUMO-conjugated TRF2 for ubiquitination through SUMO-interacting motifs (SIMs) [[cite:PUB00093834]]. Furthermore, RNF4 can form a complex with a Ubc13-ubiquitin conjugate and Ube2V2. It catalyzes K63-linked polyubiquitination by the Ube2V2-Ubc13 (ubiquitin-loaded) complex [[cite:PUB00093837]]. Meanwhile, RNF4 negatively regulates nuclear factor kappa B (NF-kappaB) signaling by down-regulating transforming growth factor beta (TGF-beta)-activated kinase 1 (TAK1)-TAK1-binding protein2 (TAB2) [[cite:PUB00093835]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "2xeu", "name" "Ring domain"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR23041" "RING FINGER DOMAIN-CONTAINING"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase RNF4", "short" "RNF4"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 7, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1330, "taxa" 5163, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 2790, "sets" 0, "proteins" 2790, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1888}, "pathways" 7}, :int